<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Raktify sitemap (static).

  Lists publicly-crawlable pages — the SPA's authenticated routes are
  excluded (they're behind a JWT anyway + blocked in robots.txt).

  Per-community public pages (/community/:slug) are NOT listed here in
  v1 because the slug list is dynamic. Two future options:
    a) Backend endpoint /sitemap-communities.xml that lists active +
       public communities, referenced from this file via <sitemapindex>.
    b) Static-prerender + commit one entry per community.
  Both can land when community count is large enough to matter.
-->
